Show HN: Get product feedback directly in your web app
text:
As a front-end engineer that worked in multiple product teams, there are a lot of discussions between PM/Designers/Engineers made to ensure everyone's aligned before features/fixes are shipped.

I'm building a tool to make this process easier, so teams can ship faster. Ditch the screenshots/screen recordings, and simplify communication in a single tool.

Got some features in mind, but I wanted to get some thoughts from the HN community.

Thanks for checking it out! Happy to answer any questions.

Ask HN: HTML Print Pagination?
text:
I am so impressed with how far we have come with HTML and CSS over the years. But printing still leaves orphaned headers at the bottom of pages and splits paragraphs so that 1% of my paragraph is on a page by itself.

<p> and <h*> are the bread and butter of semantic text on the web. Is there still no way of heuristically placing them on the printed page, in a way that looks typographically reasonable?

Ask HN: Should the text for text-only posts really be light gray?
text:
It reflexively makes it look like the post has been downvoted, as it matches the color degradation that downvoted comments experience. It's also much harder to read, even for me with perfectly good vision.

I suspect this wasn't intentional in the first place?
